headline: FactSet Unveils AI Doc Ingest As Private Capital Pressures Mount

headline: Philip Morris Stock Edges Up. Why Soft Revenue Isn’t a Drag for the Tobacco Giant.
summary: Philip Morris International  reported softer-than-expected quarterly revenue Friday, but the tobacco giant’s stock still edged higher.  Shares of the cigarette and Zyn nicotine pouch maker climbed 0.9% to $183.64.  The move came after Philip Morris reported adjusted earnings of $1.70 a share in the fourth quarter, as revenue climbed 6.8% from a year ago to $10.36 billion.

headline: Consumer Sentiment Improves in February
summary: Consumer sentiment got a better-than-expected start to February as Americans’ inflation expectations edged lower.  The University of Michigan’s consumer sentiment index came in at a reading of 57.3 for February, according to preliminary results released Friday.  Inflation expectations for the year ahead fell to 3.5% in February from 4% in January, marking the lowest reading since January 2025.
